onder if I should test with a nested interface at the top level to avoid reflection. Instantiating an object with Class.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance implies reflection, which isn't allowed in tests. I see that using MethodHandles could also engage in dynamic loading but still relies on reflection. The public API wants instances, and that complicates things further. Maybe test reflection won’t be counted in user-code-filter, but it seems tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring reflection alternatives**\\n\\nI'm trying to work within the rule that prohibits direct reflection. It seems using Class#getDeclaredConstructor might count as reflection. So, could I generate a factory class instead? I could define class bytes or even use java.util.ServiceLoader, but that might not provide a better solution. I'm considering MethodHandles instead of reflection; maybe I can use MethodHandles.publicLookup().findConstructor() for that. It feels complicated because I also need metadata, but it seems necessary. I'll need to ensure exception handling for Throwable in my tests as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading approach**\\n\\nI’m dealing with a potential native unsupported error. One option I’m thinking about is creating a private static final class called DebuggerListenerClassLoader that extends ClassLoader. This way, I can potentially define the debugger listener using the defineClass method with specific class name and bytes. It feels like a straightforward approach but I want to make sure I handle any errors effectively as I move forward with this strategy.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bVuq33w5U28pi3VQlAFspOWp|fc_052dc07321e7ec2a0169f4ebe70fe0819396ac85837005a5ba", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/reflect-config.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 484, "output": 947, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29079, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777658840561, "responseId": "resp_052dc07321e7ec2a0169f4ebd9043881939189717b4f39f3e9"}}
